# MHFT Brand and Voice

- Write in a calm, compassionate, trustworthy tone for teens and caregivers.
- Keep copy clear at an accessible reading level without sounding clinical or cold.
- Avoid fear-based language, shame framing, or exaggerated urgency.
- Do not make medical guarantees or outcome promises.
- Prefer supportive, action-oriented CTAs that reduce friction for first contact.
- Include practical trust signals where relevant (insurance, privacy, credentials, process).
